        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "Getting the Next Question Correctly",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "6043 Algebra learners, 7265 Dybuster learners, 77 Physics learners, 1581 Math learners, ",
          "Number Representation, Subtraction, Physics, Algebra, Spelling",
          "Answer of Sequences",
          "[Sequences of Answers]",
          "BKT is unable to identify relationships between skills since it requires the construction of one model per skill.",
          "The authors embloy Dynamic Bayesian Networks to map hierarchies of skills. An advantage of the method is that skills are modeled jointly.\n\n\n\n",
          "The DBN uses Log-Linear weights associated to each skill and knowledge component.",
          "DBNc1, DBNc2, DBNc3, DBNc4, BKTc, AFM, PFA",
          "10-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "Number Representation\n{RMSE: 0.4378 - DBNc4, AUC: 0.7026 - DBNc2, Reliability: 0.073 - BKTc, Resolution: 0.09 - AFM}\n\nSubtraction\n{RMSE: 0.4215 - DBNc2, AUC: 0.6928 - DBNc4, Reliability: 0.073 - DBN, Resolution: 0.09 - AFM}\n\nPhysics\n{RMSE: 0.4244 - DBNc3, AUC: 0.7021 - DBNc3, Reliability: 0.01 - DBN, Resolution: 0.03 - DBN}\n\nAlgebra\n{RMSE: 0.3246 - DBNc2, AUC: 0.7042 - DBNc2, Reliability: 0.02 - DBN, Resolution: 0.015 - DBN}\n\nSpelling\n{RMSE: 0.4472 - DBNc4, AUC: 0.5808 - DBNc4, Reliability: 0.028 - PFA, Resolution: 0.015 - AFM}\n",
          "Authors check whether their proposed model otperforms other approaches using RMSE and AUC metrics but, additionally, they also test thheir moddel when it comes to Reliability and Resolution.\n\n",
          "Model does not include ability to forget, something which is known to improve model performance. \n\n"
        ]
      ],
